{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The spectra with one or more missing atmospheric parameters or their uncertainties are removed from our sample.",
    "The MRS spectra with high signal-to-noise ratio (S/N) are required to reduce the uncertainties of the derived activity indices of the Hα line (see Section 4) as well as to reduce the uncertainties of the stellar atmospheric parameters.",
    "In this work, for the red band of MRS (denoted by R; which contains the Hα line) we use the S/N condition of S/N R ≥ 80; if the stellar atmospheric parameters in the LAMOST MRS Parameter Catalog are determined by the blue band data of MRS, the S/N condition for the blue band (denoted by B) is further requested, which is S/N B ≥ 50.",
    "This S/N condition is optimized for the analysis of MRS Hα spectra of F-, G-, and K-type stars (see He et al 2023).",
    "Note that the LAMOST MRS Parameter Catalog only provides the S/N values (snr parameter in the catalog) for the MRS band (R or B) utilized to determine the stellar atmospheric parameters."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "This S/N condition is optimized for the analysis of MRS Hα spectra of F-, G-, and K-type stars (see He et al 2023)."
  ]
}